Haan, main aapko ek basic "Age Calculator" website banane ke liye HTML, CSS, aur JavaScript code ka ek example de sakta hoon. Dhyan dein ki yeh ek simple example hai, aur ismein aur bhi advanced features aur stylings ko implement kiya ja sakta hai jaise ki responsive design, better user interface elements, etc.

### HTML (index.html)

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Age Calculator</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">
    <h2>Age Calculator</h2>
    <label for="birthdate">Enter Your Birthdate:</label>
    <input type="date" id="birthdate">
    <button onclick="calculateAge()">Calculate Age</button>
    <p id="output"></p>
</div>
<script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

### CSS (style.css)

```css
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    height: 100vh;
    background-color: #f0f2f5;
}

.container {
    background: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
}
```

### JavaScript (script.js)

```javascript
function calculateAge() {
    var birthdate = new Date(document.getElementById("birthdate").value);
    var today = new Date();
    var age = today.getFullYear() - birthdate.getFullYear();
    var m = today.getMonth() - birthdate.getMonth();
    if (m < 0 || (m === 0 && today.getDate() < birthdate.getDate())) {
        age--;
    }
    document.getElementById("output").innerHTML = `Your Age is: ${age} years old.`;
}
```

### Kaise Kaam Karta Hai:

- **HTML** mein user se unka birthdate input ke roop mein manga jaata hai aur ek button diya gaya hai jo calculateAge JavaScript function ko call karta hai jab click kiya jaata hai.
- **CSS** mein basic styling ki gayi hai taaki webpage achha dikhe.
- **JavaScript** function calculateAge ko define kiya gaya hai jo user dwara diye gaye birthdate ko lekar aaj ke date ke hisaab se age calculate karta hai aur result ko webpage par display karta hai.

Yeh example simple hai lekin aap ise as a base lekar aur bhi advanced features jaise error handling, leap year consideration, aur better UI/UX designs add kar sakte hain.

Ek advanced "Age Calculator" website banane ke liye, hum responsive design, better error handling, aur kuch user-friendly features jod sakte hain. Hum Bootstrap ka upyog karke responsive design laagu karenge, aur JavaScript mein kuch validation aur error messages bhi add karenge.

### Advanced Website Code:

#### HTML (index.html):
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Advanced Age Calculator</title>
    <link href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container mt-5">
        <h2 class="text-center mb-4">Advanced Age Calculator</h2>
        <div class="form-group">
            <label for="birthdate">Enter Your Birthdate:</label>
            <input type="date" class="form-control" id="birthdate">
        </div>
        <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="calculateAge()">Calculate Age</button>
        <p id="output" class="mt-3"></p>
    </div>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```
#### CSS (style.css):
```css
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    background-color: #f0f2f5;
}

.container {
    background: #fff;
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
    max-width: 500px;
    margin: auto;
}
```
#### JavaScript (script.js):
```javascript
function calculateAge() {
    var birthdate = document.getElementById("birthdate").value;
    if (!birthdate) {
        document.getElementById("output").innerHTML = "Please enter your birthdate.";
        return;
    }

    var birthdateDate = new Date(birthdate);
    var today = new Date();
    var age = today.getFullYear() - birthdateDate.getFullYear();
    var m = today.getMonth() - birthdateDate.getMonth();
    if (m < 0 || (m === 0 && today.getDate() < birthdateDate.getDate())) {
        age--;
    }

    if (age < 0) {
        document.getElementById("output").innerHTML = "The selected date is in the future!";
    } else {
        document.getElementById("output").innerHTML = `You are ${age} years old.`;
    }
}
```
Is code mei hum Bootstrap 4.5.2 ka use kar rahe hain taki responsive design ho jo mobile aur desktop dono par achhi tarah se kaam kare. `style.css` mei, basic styling ke saath container ko center me rakhne ke liye additional styling di gayi hai.

`script.js` mei, humne error handling bhi add ki hai, jaise ki agar user birthdate input nahi karta ya future ki date select karta hai, toh us case mei appropriate message show kiya jayega.

Yeh ek basic se advanced level ki website ke transition ka example hai. Aur bhi functionalities jaise ki precise age including months and days, leap year considerations, aur user experience ko improve karne ke liye further customizations aur enhancements kiye ja sakte hain.

Agar upar di gayi code snippets mein age calculate karne par output nahi aa raha hai, to yeh sambhav hai ki ek minor issue ho jo overlook ho gaya ho ya environment setup mein kuch chhoot gaya ho. Yahan ek revised aur simplified version hai jo direct output pradarshit karega jab user apni birthdate enter karega aur "Calculate Age" button press karega. Ye snippet directly output dikhane par focus karta hai:

### HTML:
Yahi rahega, koi parivartan nahi. Bas sunishchit karein ki `index.html`, `style.css`, aur `script.js` teeno ko apne local environment mei sahi se setup kiya gaya hai.

### JavaScript (script.js):
```javascript
function calculateAge() {
    var birthdate = document.getElementById("birthdate").value;
    if (!birthdate) {
        document.getElementById("output").innerHTML = "Please enter your birthdate.";
        return;
    }

    var birthdateDate = new Date(birthdate);
    var today = new Date();
    var age = today.getFullYear() - birthdateDate.getFullYear();
    var monthDifference = today.getMonth() - birthdateDate.getMonth();
    if (monthDifference < 0 || (monthDifference === 0 && today.getDate() < birthdateDate.getDate())) {
        age--;
    }

    document.getElementById("output").innerHTML = age < 0 ? "Please enter a valid birthdate." : `You are ${age} years old.`;
}
```
Yadi output abhi bhi nahi aata hai, to kuch debugging steps aap try kar sakte hain:

1. **Console Check:** Browser ke developer tools (F12 key ya right-click ➜ "Inspect" option aur phir "Console" tab) mei jaake dekhein ki koi JavaScript errors to nahi show ho rahe hain.
2. **Browser Compatibility:** Sunishchit karein ki aapka browser HTML5 `<input type="date">` element ko support karta hain. Kuch purane browsers mei yeh properly support nahi karta.
3. **File Paths:** Sunishchit karein ki `script.js` aur `style.css` files sahi path par hain aur `index.html` se sahi tarah linked hain.

Yadi aap saare steps sahi se follow karte hain aur code sahi se setup karte hain, to yeh simple age calculator function properly kaam karna chahiye.
